this is similar to issues we saw with kernel builds on ppc and s390, seems to be related to some parallel make or file access. I have just fixed same issue in highlight on s390 by resubmitting the build.

This bug appears to have been reported against 'rawhide' during the Fedora 24 development cycle. Changing version to '24'.
More information and reason for this action is here: https://fedoraproject.org/wiki/Fedora_Program_Management/HouseKeeping/Fedora24#Rawhide_Rebase
despite the fact that I did a lot of testing / mock compilations against x86_64 (through all f22, f23, f24 and rawhide releases), unfortunately i686 looks broken, I'll take a look further soon.
The code doesn't seem to be broken, it's the buildsystem. Try with disabling parallel make/build.
This package has changed ownership in the Fedora Package Database. Reassigning to the new owner of this component.
Looks like this was fixed by disabling parallel build?
IIRC no one touched the spec, just trying the build couple times and it passes at the end. But disabling parallel build would be safer.
